List of all Locality/Suburbs, Postal Area (POA) and Local Government Areas (LGA) intersections present in sf structures. You can use this dataset to build filter tables for load_map()

Source: R/data.R
locations.table.Rd

List of all Locality/Suburbs, Postal Area (POA) and Local Government Areas (LGA) intersections present in sf structures. You can use this dataset to build filter tables for load_map()

locations.table

Format

A data frame with 9 variables:

LOC_PID

Unique ID for each locality/suburb (taken from data.gov.au)

LGA_PID

Unique ID for each local government area (taken from data.gov.au)

LGA

Name of local government area (e.g. Moreland)

LOCALITY

Name of locality or suburb (e.g. Brunswick)

State.Region

Name of "official" region within the state (e.g. Greater Metropolitan Melbourne))

ABB_NAME

Suburb name in uppercase

Metro.Region

Internal subdivision in Metro areas, if applies (.e.g Inner Metropolitan Melbourne)

State

State or Territory (.e.g Victoria)

POA_CODE16

Postal Area Code, as defined by ABS, (e.g. 3056)

Source

https://data.gov.au/
